metadata.title: Listening Guide - Bartók's Concerto for Orchestra Part 1-V1lxqcG5ZeY.opus
metadata.excerpt: During the WWII Hungarian composer Bela Bartok fled to America hoping to forge a new career but he failed to make much impact and became seriously ill. Soon after he was diagnosed as having leukemia. Whilst in hospital Bartok was visited by Serge Koussevitzky, the conductor of the Boston Symphony Orchestra. He asked Bartok for a new work, uncertain if it would ever be written but hoping that the advance would help cover some of Bartok's medical expenses.
